I have a weird error which is from a large script, not easily reducible. But the stack trace ends like this:
```ERROR: TypeError: in new, expected Union, got Type{Tuple{Union{Base.KeySet{Symbol, Dict{Symbol, Any}}, Set{Symbol}}, Int64}}
Stacktrace:
   [1] Base.Fix2(f::typeof(isequal), x::Type{Union{Tuple{Base.KeySet{Symbol, Dict{Symbol, Any}}, Int64}, Tuple{Set{Symbol}, Int64}}})```
In the error, it looks like Fix2 got passed a tuple of a Union, but in the stack trace, it shows a union of a tuple. What's up with that?
